Advantages of NAT
Conserves public IPv4 addresses.
Allows multiple devices to share one public IP.
Hides internal network addresses from external networks.
Improves basic network security.
Simplifies private network management.
Disadvantages of NAT
Adds processing overhead on the router.
Some applications require additional NAT configuration.
Can complicate troubleshooting.
NAT in AWS

AWS provides a NAT Gateway to allow instances in private subnets to access the Internet (for updates or downloads) without exposing them to incoming Internet traffic.

Example:

